                            <comment id="14254232" author="jjg" created="Wed, 27 Mar 2019 14:39:16 -0700"  >If you go with something like what you propose:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; cannot assign a value to static final field g; did you mean to initialize it in a static initializer block or static field initializer? &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
it should be structured as a main diagnostic and a subdiagnostic.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
That being said, the &amp;quot;did you mean...&amp;quot; is a bit folksy.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
A different way of getting the information across would be something like:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; cannot assign a value to static final field g except with a field initializer or in a static initializer block&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
and even that could arguably be split into a primary diagnostic and a sub diagnostic&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
cannot assign a value to static final field g&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;not a field initializer or in static initializer block&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
